// go.work ties the two CLI extension modules and their shared module together
// for local development (editor tooling, cross-module `go test ./...`). It is
// DEV-ONLY: each consumer module also carries a `replace` directive pointing at
// ../shared, so `go build`/`go test` work with GOWORK=off and inside a single
// module too. The shared module is consumed via a relative replace while the
// CLIs live in this monorepo; when an extension is split into its own repo the
// replace is swapped for a published version (see CLEANUP_PLAN.md Phase 5a).
go 1.26

use (
	./cli/gh-student
	./cli/gh-teacher
	./cli/shared
)
